## 5. Common Cyberattacks & Solutions

### ğŸ”¥ Major Cyberattacks
- **Malware** â†’ Viruses, worms, trojans, spyware.  
  âœ… Solution: Antivirus, patching, firewalls, behavior monitoring.  

- **Phishing** â†’ Fake emails/websites tricking users.  
  âœ… Solution: Email filters, user training, 2FA.  

- **Password Attacks** â†’ Brute force, credential stuffing.  
  âœ… Solution: Strong passwords, MFA, password managers.  

- **DDoS (Distributed Denial of Service)** â†’ Flooding servers with traffic.  
  âœ… Solution: Load balancers, DDoS mitigation services (Cloudflare, AWS Shield).  

- **Man-in-the-Middle (MITM)** â†’ Intercepting communication.  
  âœ… Solution: HTTPS, VPN, encryption, secure Wi-Fi.  

- **Drive-by Download** â†’ Malicious code auto-installed from websites.  
  âœ… Solution: Updated browsers, disable auto-downloads, endpoint security.  

- **Malvertising** â†’ Malware spread via online ads.  
  âœ… Solution: Ad blockers, secure ad networks, anti-malware.  

- **Rogue Software (Fake Antivirus)** â†’ Tricks user to install malware.  
  âœ… Solution: Awareness, allow only trusted software, EDR.  

### âš¡ Other Attacks
- SQL Injection  
- Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)  
- Insider Attacks  
- Supply Chain Attacks  

